# Braces for every block

Use **`{ }` around the body** of every control-flow statement (`if`, `else`, `for`, `foreach`, `while`, `do`, `using` when multi-line matters, `fixed`, etc.), even when the body is a single statement.

Do **not** omit braces for “one-liners” — it avoids subtle bugs when someone adds a second line later.

## Examples

```csharp
// ❌ BAD
if (x == null)
    return Result.Failure(error);

// ✅ GOOD
if (x == null)
{
    return Result.Failure(error);
}
```

```csharp
// ❌ BAD
foreach (var id in ids)
    await ProcessAsync(id);

// ✅ GOOD
foreach (var id in ids)
{
    await ProcessAsync(id);
}
```

Exception: **expression-bodied members** (`=>`) are fine when they are a single expression, not a block:

```csharp
public string Name => _name;
```
